\frac{(x^3+x^2+2x-2)}{(x^2-1)}=x+1+\frac{3x-1}{x^2-1} 
\frac{(x^3+x^2+2x-2)}{(x^2-1)}=x + 1 + \frac{3x-1}{x^2-1}
