x + 1 + \frac{3x-1}{(x - 1)(x+ 1)} = \frac A{x-1} + \frac B{x + 1}
A(x+1) + B(x - 1) = (A + B)x + (A - B) = 3x - 1 
\iff A+ B = 3 \;\; \text{and}\;\; A - B = -1
A, B
A = B - 1 \implies 2B - 1 = 3 \iff B = 2 \implies A = 1
\frac{(x^3+x^2+2x-2)}{(x^2-1)}=x + 1 + \frac 1{x-1} + \frac 2{x + 1}
\frac{x^{3}+x^{2}+2x-2}{x^{2}-1}=x+1+\frac{3x-1}{x^{2}-1}=x+1+\frac{3x-1}{(x-1)(x+1)}.\tag{1}
