\frac{1}{x-1}=-\frac{1}{1-x}=-\sum_{n=1}^{\infty }x^{n-1},\quad \frac{1}{x+1}=\frac{1}{1+x}=\sum_{n=1}^{\infty }(-1)^{n-1}x^{x-1},
\tag{7}
\frac{1}{1-x}=\sum_{n=1}^{\infty }x^{n-1},\qquad (|x|<1).\tag{8}
